<subSubSection id="C36F650CFFC1FFCDFC40FEBC1325C00F" pageId="22" pageNumber="719" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="8BCA3687FFC1FFCDFC40FEBC1260C21F" blockId="22.[904,1323,305,327]" box="[904,1323,305,327]" pageId="22" pageNumber="719">
<heading id="D08281EBFFC1FFCDFC40FEBC1260C21F" box="[904,1323,305,327]" centered="true" fontSize="9" level="2" pageId="22" pageNumber="719" reason="2">
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFC1FFCDFC40FEBC1260C21F" authority="(SAY, 1829)" baseAuthorityName="Say" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[904,1323,305,327]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="719" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="posticum">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC1FFCDFC40FEBC13D1C21D" box="[904,1178,306,327]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="719">COPESTYLUM POSTICUM</emphasis>
(SAY, 1829)
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCA3687FFC1FFCDFCEEFED71325C00F" blockId="22.[806,1422,344,855]" pageId="22" pageNumber="719">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC1FFCDFCEEFED7136BC235" box="[806,1056,344,366]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="719">Larva and puparium:</emphasis>
Anterior fold with a wide band of spicules. Metathorax with two groups of a few indistinct spicules on the anteroventral margin. Dorsal vestiture comprising evenly sized setae except for anterodorsal groups of large, broad setae on the mesothorax and metathorax and smaller setae on middle transverse bands on abdominal segments 1–2. Abdominal segments 4–6 with second row of crochets inconspicuous and not as developed as on abdominal segments 1–3. Posterior breathing tube red-brown at base, dark brown at apex, below TR tube nodulate, above coriaceous. AP about a third as high to spiky rim as wide at TR. Pupal spiracles approximated about as far apart as a pupal spiracle is wide and slightly curved in upper third (
<figureCitation id="134E2A02FFC1FFCDFB7BFC8A124EC042" box="[1203,1285,772,794]" captionStart="Figures 68–73" captionStartId="51.[164,254,1558,1577]" captionTargetBox="[323,1283,195,1525]" captionTargetId="figure-0@51.[323,1283,195,1528]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="Figures 68–73. Puparia of Copestylum, scanning electron photomicrographs, scales as indicated on images. 68, 70, Copestylum macrocephalum; 68, posterior breathing tube (prp), dorsal view width of TR = 1.3 mm; 70, prp, apical; 71, Copestylum posticum; pupal spiracles, dorsal view length = 0.93 mm; 69, 72–73, Copestylum isabellina; 69, prp, dorsal view width at TR = 1.1 mm, 72, pupal spiracles, ventrolateral view length 0.82 mm; 73, spiracular openings, apical and lateral views." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443518" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443518/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="719">Fig. 71</figureCitation>
). Openings coating upper half of one side, those at the apex without a lateral projection.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36F650CFFC1FFCDFCEEFC0C1261C650" pageId="22" pageNumber="719" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCA3687FFC1FFCDFCEEFC0C14BAC749" blockId="22.[806,1421,897,1041]" pageId="22" pageNumber="719">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC1FFCDFCEEFC0C14A1C0CF" box="[806,1002,898,919]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="719">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
Very similar in larval characters to 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFC1FFCDFCEEFC2E14F0C0ED" baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1887" box="[806,955,928,949]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="719" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="isabellina">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC1FFCDFCEEFC2E14F0C0ED" box="[806,955,928,949]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="719">C. isabellina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from which 
<taxonomicName id="4C754D04FFC1FFCDFB91FC2E13AFC0ED" baseAuthorityName="Say" baseAuthorityYear="1829" box="[1113,1252,928,949]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="22" pageNumber="719" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="posticum">
<emphasis id="B901EA95FFC1FFCDFB91FC2E13AFC0ED" box="[1113,1252,928,949]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="719">C. posticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in the pupal spiracles being close, about as far apart as a spiracle is wide, and the openings at the apex lacking spiky projections.
</paragraph>
